<title>INDIA: India's National bourse index to see some changes.</title>
<headline>India's National bourse index to see some changes.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>The benchmark index of the National Stock Exchange is being altered this month to introduce three actively traded stocks, officials said.</p>
<p>They said telecommunications firm Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd will replace Brooke Bond from the new account on May 7.</p>
<p>Oil stock Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd and electrical equipment firm Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltd will be introduced in the 50-stocks index from May 14, replacing SCICI Ltd and Dr Reddy's Laboratories respectively.</p>
<p>-- Bombay newsroom +91-22-265 9000</p>
